A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 State Retirement and Pension System – Military Service Credit – Eligibility
3 FOR the purpose of authorizing certain members of the State Retirement and Pension
4 System to receive credit for certain military service if the member receives military
5 service credit in another retirement system; prohibiting an individual from receiving
6 credit more than a certain number of times; and generally relating to members of
7 the State Retirement and Pension System receiving military service credit.
8 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
9 Article – State Personnel and Pensions
10 Section 38–104
11 Annotated Code of Maryland
12 (2024 Replacement Volume and 2024 Supplement)
13 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
14 That the Laws of Maryland read as follows:
15 Article – State Personnel and Pensions
16 38–104.
17 (a) (1) This section applies to an individual who is:
18 (i) a member of a State system; or
19 (ii) a former member of a State system who is eligible to receive a
20 benefit under § 29–302 or § 29–303 of this article.
21 (2) This section does not apply to a retiree of a State system.
